      company_url: "http://www.neonomics.io",
      location: "@Oslo",
      title: "Site Reliability Engineer",
      description: "<p><strong>Are you interested in automation and FinTech?</strong></p>\n<p><em>Fresh out of the Nordics in 2016, Neonomics (meaning “New Economy”) was founded as a direct response to the impending challenges facing the banking industry during its radical transition into the era of open banking. We are building a high-value ecosystem of fintech solutions for the next generation of financial services and today we are connected to more than 1300 banks within the EU, with the connections built on our unique API integration technology.</em></p>\n<p>We are now looking for a Site Reliability Engineer to join our Neonomics family. In this position you will work with Agile engineering teams to provide production insight into running and operating software at-scale in a globally distributed highly available cloud based system. You will guide the team to consider scale-out implications and operational support implications of the choices they make during the development cycle, and you will play a hands-on role helping the team meet ambitious technical, operational, schedule, and business requirements.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Aid in building and supporting a container based platform architecture that can ensure microservice teams can own their code all the way into production.</li>\n<li>Build and support tooling and automated infrastructure necessary to deliver metrics from production environments, deploy releases to production environments, and manage multiple versions of multiple microservices operating in tandem to produce a fully functional system.</li>\n<li>Work with a team of backend and application development engineers to further institutionalize the notion of the team owns their code in production and offer suggestions on how to better do that in the context of the development sprint work.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>About you:</strong></p>\n<p>To succeed in this position, we believe that you are system thinker with a passion for creating products that deliver incredible customer experiences. We wish that you have experience with operational automation and data driven metrics collection, and it is important that you have a true desire to automate it rather than do it repeatedly.</p>\n<p>We also wish that you have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience running an at-scale global cloud based application in AWS or Google Cloud platforms with Docker and Kubernetes.</li>\n<li>Experience automating in Python, Ruby or rapid-development languages as well as infrastructure as code.</li>\n<li>Experience in networking protocols, IP routing issues, TLS and diagnosing routing or high-level network transactional issues through logs and metrics.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why work with us?</strong></p>\n<p>Besides having the warmest, funniest and the most including colleges, we can offer the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A start-up environment and mentality where your voice is important and will be heard.</li>\n<li>A flat structure with direct access to decision makers.</li>\n<li>A highly stimulating cross-functional team environment with more than 15 nationalities and plenty of opportunities for personal and professional development.</li>\n<li>Relaxed environment with informal dress code.</li>\n<li>A lot of social activities like Fintalks, dinners and Friday-beers.</li>\n<li>And of course, we offer competitive salary and benefits, ex. 7% pension benefit.\n </li>\n</ul>\n",
      how_to_apply: "<p><a href=\"https://candidate.hr-manager.net/ApplicationInit.aspx?cid=2129&amp;ProjectId=143588&amp;DepartmentId=18957&amp;MediaId=5\">Apply for this position</a></p>\n",
